My husband and I usually visit NYC a few times a year. We started a tradition of getting a combo platter from one of The Halal Guys food carts and having a picnic in Central Park. Due to the pandemic, we haven't been able to go to NYC since 2019 and I've been missing it like crazy. Yesterday we had to go into DC for work and decided to grab lunch. We looked up restaurants near us and were stoked to find The Halal Guys had a location here!! We ordered a combo platter and a chicken gyro through the app. Of course with extra white sauce and hot sauce (duh!) We arrived and it was ready for us. I checked the bag and the order was perfect, nothing missing, and they even threw in an extra white sauce. I'm sure that was an accident, but I'll take it! We got home and the food was still warm and delicious. While it wasn't NYC, it gave us a little taste of our favorite city that we've been missing so much. Good service. Good food. You can't go wrong visiting this restaurant.
